## Running the iflow

Scenario 1: Standalone usage
cd $WORKAREA
setenv CHEETAH_RTL_ROOT = /p/hdk/cad/Cheetah-RTL/2021.06.fe.Bento.1.77/bento

$CHEEATH_RTL_ROOT/iflow/scripts/iflow_run.pl -ini <path to ini file> -gen_only
make -f Makefile.iflow -j 4 run_all_stages

An example of the input INI file is example/iflow.ini

Scenario 2: Usage through GK

An example of usage of iflow is example/Gkutils.cfg

After the changes in the Gkutils is done,
    * You can run MockTurnin
    * You can run Turnin
    * You can run it as a Flow Manager using the following command :
        ^ /p/hdk/rtl/proj_tools/gatekeeper_utils/1.01.76/gk-utils.pl -cfgdir /path/to/cfgdir -proj cth -cfm_modelroot $WORKAREA -c <design name> -s <stage> -branch <branch>
	^ Use option [-load_task_norun] to just load the task and manually run from nbflow GUI.
	^ To run locally and not in netbatch, do "setenv CTH_FM_LOCAL"
